    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Dealing With D.S.L.</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jonathan Feldberg letter on May 4 article scores Bell Atlantic's failure to offer New York customers who sign up for its DSL service local dial-up number</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>The D.S.L. article did not point out the lack of a local dial-up phone number for connecting to the Internet through Bell Atlantic if you live in New York. That's right, when you sign up for D.S.L. service from Bell Atlantic in New York and your service is down, you have to dial New Jersey if you want to connect using a modem. There ought to be a law.</p>
        <p>JONATHAN FELDBERG  Dobbs Ferry, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
